    </p>
  </task>
  <task>
    <p>
      Explain in your own words what <m>\displaystyle\int_{-C} f \enspace ds = \int_C f \enspace ds</m> means in the Copium analogy. It may be helpful to describe each side of the equation separately and say why they are equal in the analogy.
    </p>
  </task>
  <task>
