      Explain in your own words what <m>\displaystyle\int_{C_1+C_2} f \enspace ds = \int_{C_1} f \enspace ds + \int_{C_2} f \enspace ds</m> means in the Copium analogy. It may be helpful to describe each side of the equation separately and say why they are equal in the analogy.
    </p>
